        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-02-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                <head>No. 1.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Schenck</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 2,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>London journals all demand that United States shall withdraw claims for
                            indirect damages, as not within intention of Treaty. Ministry alarmed.
                            Am exerting myself with hope to prevent anything rash or offensive being
                            done or said by this Government. Evarts here cooperating.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SCHENCK.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
